  },
  {
    n: 5,
    title: "Clad the room and build the benches",
    body: "Use a rot-resistant, aromatic wood like Western red cedar (or budget Nordic spruce) on walls and ceiling, and a low-conductivity wood that stays cool to the touch - <strong>aspen or abachi</strong> - on bench surfaces. Never use resinous, knotty pine where skin touches it: the resin liquefies at sauna heat and creates sticky, burning hot spots. Build tiered benches so you can sit higher where it is hotter. See <a href=\"#materials\">wood &amp; materials</a>.",
